<item>
            <title>[SOLR-5636] SolrRequestParsers does some xpath lookups on every request.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5636</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This seems a bit wasteful for one, but also, under heavy load, with lots of cores on a node, I&apos;ve seen this xpath parsing randomly fail with weird nullpointer exceptions. Perhaps depends on the xml parser you end up using. Anyway, it&apos;s easy to work around and avoid the parsing everytime solrdispatchfilter is hit by just doing it up front once.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
